<br>
Oh, and how the hell are we trying to ruin the calendar by saying that.  Sorry but its only an opinion.  It's not like were saying were gonna FFA Hate and Fear, every day of the week till our guild has got all their epics and twinks outfitted.  And even if not allowing them to post for 30 days was the right thing to do, making their next raid which was already posted void was extreame to say the least and is probably why this whole thing has went on for so long.  If the admins let them have that day most of this would have been forgotten already.  So its a lesson for all to be learned, and hopefully improved upon.<br>
<br>
My opinion here and since its a flame board who cares.<br>
<br>
BB rotation is BS.  If my guild has met the required 40 planeable thing, its my day, my raid, so keep your nose out.<br>
<br>
If a guild/alliance has met the 40 planable rule, well they should be able to do what ever they want in the planes.  Sure the 6 guild invite thing was made for a reason, but think about it for a minute.  When was this rule actually made, probably when we still had the planable thing at 18.  And if I have 40 accounts 46+ how many others do you actually think I'll invite.  Not many because of LD's.  So a guild should be able to invite who they want, when they want.  The piggyback thing no longer applies because your not gonna have much more than 40 in the zone at the best of times, and a lower number is probably preferred, so invites will probably never be more than 10 from any other guild.<br>
<br>
Keep the 40 planable rule, keep the 2am rule and trash the rest.  Keeps the admins jobs easier, allows the people who posted on that day to have fun.  And may even allow for more FFA days, because if a God ain't up, a certain guild may just decide that doing the plane isn't worth it, and open it up for who ever wants it.  It could make many happy, reduce a lot of the flames, and just allow people to have fun without all the hastle.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion, and I'm not trying to ruin this calendar.  Just figure some things need to be changed. <p>  Only in death are our souls set free.<br>
