</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did I play my charecter this long...</span><hr size=1> Tarv:  I have never known you to be disrespectful to me or any of my guildmates.  Indeed, last time you wandered into our chat channel, you seemed oddly overcourteous for an Ogre by telling me you would be leaving our channel before I even had a chance to wonder who you were.  I appreciate the respect you have shown other players whenever I have seen you.<br>
<br>
Kathrynn:  Ouch, *some* honor?  I try and act as honorable as possible, I'd like to think I am somewhat successful.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I will miss you when you head off to the other server.  We've had a lot of good times, I wish you the best.<br>
<br>
Marcys:  It's Noble Blade, use spell check, and you will look less like an ass.  As for the Calendar making NB what it is today, get off yer high horse and stop belittling others' accomplishments simply because you had nothing to do with them.  The Calendar had nothing to do with all the effort put in by my guildmates and I over the past year.  You have never been on a Noble Blade raid, so claiming you know anything about why or how we are successful is pure bullshit.  <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Noble Blade has enjoyed as much of the Calendar's advantages as its disadvantages, much like everyone else, nothing more.  We are no different than anyone in that we have been able to do our planes raids in peace, but because of that compromise have only seen 3 Innoruuks and 4 Cazic Thules in the last 14 months that luck threw our way.  But don't for one second think that we owe our recent success to the Calendar anymore than KEG does.  Despite all our recent success, we still believe in the validity of this Calendar as it was originally intended.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp We aren't a &quot;Pseudo Uber&quot; guild, nor will we ever reach &quot;Full Uberness&quot;, because I share Elaundar's definition of an &quot;Uberguild&quot; and as such it is nothing I want to be a part of.  As long as I am GM of Noble Blade, we won't be an &quot;Uber Guild&quot; regardless of how successful we become.  Powerful guilds don't have to treat other people like shit to be successful, maybe if you stopped looking in your mirror of hubris you would understand that.  Certainly many of your guildmates understand this, people like Bradan, Jerrica, Vashon, Snaggle, and Kathrynn come to mind.  Being a person worthy of respect has nothing to do with killing Uber_mob_X with only Z number of people.  It has to do with who is behind the keyboard and how they treat other people.  <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp You Marcys have treated everyone I know with disrespect on a consistent basis since I met you.  Me, my friends, my guildmates, random people that post on this board, all treated like they were somehow less than the &quot;wonderful&quot; Marcys because somehow you are more valuable than they.  From your pathetic oocs for groups in Seb, &quot;/ooc L 56 Paladin looking for a competent group&quot; to cancelling magic on enchanters charmed mobs and shamen's rooted creatures, or belittling others accomplishments and your crappy flames posted here.  I'm glad to be the one to waste my breath pointing out to you, that without KEG you are nothing but a childish prick who doesn't know how to treat others with simple common decency.  Think of how much shit you arrogantly give other people and how grateful you should be KEG puts up with you before you /guildremove next time.  EQ can be a lonely place when you've burnt all your bridges.<br>
<br>
So F Marcys.<br>
<br>
Jerrica:  I agree with your position that this system has become something it was never meant to be, and apologize that Sultar misunderstood what you were trying to say.  I will assert a majority of the server didn't want the BB clause and repeatedly this has been the sole cause of all this strife.  I will also put forward, that regardless of how little KEG may or may not have wanted it, they were one of the three who dictated to the server that certain guilds were &quot;more equal&quot; when it came to getting epic loot.  You were instrumental in taming down how this came about and saving the calendar.  The server owes you a great deal for your role in what could have become a very bad situation.  With the planar revamp, and the server split, I can't see why we shouldn't be able to go back to the three simple rules others have posted in this thread.  Good luck in all that you do, in EQ and in life.  I am among those who will miss you.<br>
<br>
Falc:  Lay off the poor ranger, he's got it bad enough already with always being OOM.<br>
